FBIS4-40475 "drsov117_d_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 Regional Affairs Moscow Accused of Plotting Against Chechnya Moscow Accused of Plotting Against Chechnya LD1606195594 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 1800 GMT 16 Jun 94 LD1606195594 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy Russian BFN [Text] Russia keeps organizing conspiracies against Chechnya, Chechen Foreign Minister Shamsudin Yusef said today. He accused Moscow of refusing to normalize relations between the two countries. He mentioned the recent attempt on Dzhokhar Dudayev's life as an example of anti-Groznyy actions. In the meantime, the military commandant of Chechnya has today demanded that illegal armed formations disband themselves and their leaders give themselves up. This decision by Sultan (Geleskhanov) is connected with recent clashes in Groznyy.
